.TH COMMONCRAWL "1" "April 2026" "commoncrawl v0.01" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
commoncrawl \- query common crawl cdx index
.SH DESCRIPTION
usage: commoncrawl [\-h] [\-v] [\-\-match {exact,prefix,host,domain}]
.IP
[\-\-from DATE_FROM] [\-\-to DATE_TO] [\-\-crawls CRAWLS]
[\-\-status STATUS] [\-\-outdir OUTDIR] [\-\-no\-dedup]
[\-\-limit LIMIT] [\-\-cache\-limit CACHE_LIMIT]
[\-\-browser BROWSER] [\-\-download\-only]
url
.PP
Query Common Crawl's CDX index and interactively download snapshots.
Fetches gzipped CDX shards directly from S3 (data.commoncrawl.org),
bypassing the overloaded index.commoncrawl.org HTTP API.
.SS "positional arguments:"
.TP
url
URL to look up
.SS "options:"
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
show this help message and exit
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
show program's version number and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-match\fR {exact,prefix,host,domain}
Match type (default: prefix)
.TP
\fB\-\-from\fR DATE_FROM
Earliest timestamp YYYYMMDD (inclusive); Common Crawl
data begins 20080509
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR DATE_TO
Latest timestamp YYYYMMDD (inclusive)
.TP
\fB\-\-crawls\fR CRAWLS
Only check the N most recent crawls in the date range
.TP
\fB\-\-status\fR STATUS
Filter by HTTP status (default: 200, pass '' to
disable)
.TP
\fB\-\-outdir\fR OUTDIR
Output directory (default: ./cc_snapshots)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-dedup\fR
Show every capture, not deduped by content digest
.TP
\fB\-\-limit\fR LIMIT
Max captures to display (default: 20, 0 = no limit)
.TP
\fB\-\-cache\-limit\fR CACHE_LIMIT
Max cluster.idx cache size in MB (default: 1500);
oldest entries are evicted first
.TP
\fB\-\-browser\fR BROWSER
Browser to open each saved snapshot with (default:
$BROWSER, or w3m if unset)
.TP
\fB\-\-download\-only\fR
Save snapshots to disk without opening them
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
commoncrawl 'https://example.com/' \-\-match exact \-\-crawls 1
.IP
latest crawl only, exact URL match
.IP
commoncrawl 'https://example.com/' \-\-match host \-\-from 20200101
.IP
any capture of a URL on example.com since 2020
